This article describes the setup of ''USB'' ('''U'''niversal '''S'''erial '''B'''us) controllers.

== Installation ==

=== Hardware detection ===
To choose the right driver, first detect the used USB controllers. You can use [[Hardware detection#lspci|lspci]] for this task:
{{RootCmd|lspci {{!}} grep --color -i usb}}

=== Kernel ===
You need to activate the following kernel options:
{{Kernel||<pre>
Device Drivers --->
    [*] USB support  --->
        <*>   Support for Host-side USB

        Select a USB HCI driver, e.g.:
        <*> xHCI HCD (USB 3.0) support (xhci-hcd)
        <*> EHCI HCD (USB 2.0) support (ehci-hcd)
        <*> OHCI HCD support (ohci-hcd)
        <*> UHCI HCD (most Intel and VIA) support (uhci-hcd)
</pre>}}

=== Software ===
Portage knows the global USE flag ''usb'' for enabling support for USB in other packages:
{{File|/etc/portage/make.conf||
USE{{=}}"... usb ..."
}}
After setting this you want to update your system so the changes take effect:
{{Emerge|params+=--changed-use --deep|@world}}

You also want to install {{Package|sys-apps/usbutils}}, if it isn't already pulled in:
{{Emerge|usbutils}}
The USE flags of usbutils are:
{{USEflag|package=sys-apps/usbutils
|network-cron
|python+yes
|zlib+yes
}}

